events.name: New York Knicks at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — A roar arose inside Barclays Center and for one of the few times Sunday, Kevin Durant had nothing to do with it.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant scores 53, Nets edge Knicks 110-107 as Irving watches

headlines.description: — Marcus Morris scored 31 points and Luke Kennard had 16 against their former team, helping the Los Angeles Clippers rally from an 18-point deficit to beat the Detroit Pistons 106-102 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morris, Kennard lead Clippers over Pistons, 106-102

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid and the Philadelphia 76ers brought out the best in the Orlando Magic.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid's 35 points, 16 rebounds lead 76ers over Magic in OT

headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 33 of his 47 points in the first half, and the Atlanta Hawks beat the Indiana Pacers 131-128 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trae Young scores 47, Hawks hold off Pacers 131-128

events.name: Houston Rockets at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Jonas Valanciunas had 32 points and 10 rebounds, and the New Orleans Pelicans emphatically snapped a four-game skid with a 130-105 victory over the Houston Rockets on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Valanciunas, Hayes power Pelicans past Rockets, 130-105

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Dillon Brooks had to wait a few more minutes to make his return.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies lead for all but 25 seconds in win over Thunder

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis had a few words to say about the Los Angeles Lakers' playoff loss to the Phoenix Suns last season before the teams played Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: NBA-leading Suns rout Lakers; James reaches 10,000 assists
